    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"112680\">Johan Commelin</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Zp.20is.20compact.3F/near/479413178\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The definition of <code>profinite</code> is still the topological one, right? So showing that <code>Z_[p]</code> is totally disconnected/separated should be enough. (I assume Hausdorff is done.)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Apparently I am wrong! What a nice thing to be wrong about <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f642\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span>  </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Profinite</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ_</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"c\">/-</span><span class=\"cm\"> Profinite.of ℤ_[p] : Profinite -/</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Many thanks to <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"741361\">@Jou Glasheen</span> and <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"308899\">@Yakov Pechersky</span> for adding the instances showing that Zp is compact and totally disconnected, which are the inputs to this.</p>",
